Episode 8 : Live interactive session - Navin Vasta, Delhi based Travel & Street  Photographer 
@navinvatsa  has started his journey in photography with a simple point and shoot camera with the sole intention to capture family moments almost 16 years back. But life has its own plans while you are busy with your own. After the accidental death of his wife in 2009, the loneliness and responsibilities towards his 3-year-old Son as a single parent completely consumed him and the love for photography lingered on. After years, one day while flipping through old family albums, he realized his calling and decided to become a full-time photographer and finally, he resigned from his 17 years of long academic and administrative job in a reputed University and decided to start his Photography journey. In the last 5 years, he received various awards and recognized by various International and National organizations of repute such as National Geographic, Sony World, Sony India, Camarena Academy, 121Clicks.com, HIPA, etc. He has many publications and Interviews in National and International media. He is one of the well-recognized Street and Travel Photographer from India.

He is joining our interactive session on 17th april 2020 . Shoot the questions! What are you waiting for .
.

@withmanish ,  is a professional travel, landscape and wildlife photographer. he is specialised in high altitude and cold places in the high himalayas much before it became a fashionable destination. most of the time he spends with nomads, locals in the un-touristy places in the remote region of himalayas, across india, central asia and many other places either photographing them or looking and experiencing some rare cultures. 
he is passionate about wildlife in the high himalayas. apart from that, he is an avid cyclist and took an adventure on bicycle solo to travel across india for 6 months from deserted places to the high himalayas and coastal side of the map.

Join us in the webinar session of a virtual tour to Trans Himalayas & tribes on the 19th of April at 6PM

Tania Chatterjee is a travel photographer, storyteller, and an educator. based in Kolkata. Tania has a strong acumen to portray indigenous cultural, inspiring human stories, social issues and travel stories across several states of India as well as different countries. She is the CEO and mentor of a photographic organization called FOTORBIT Pvt. Ltd. 
She is also working with UNDP as a consultant photographer; she has worked on various photographic assignments with renowned agencies like NatGeoTraveller India, VIVO India. etc, judged numerous photography contests and conduct various national and international photography workshops. Tania’s photos have been widely published and exhibited around the world, along with numerous awards.

join us in the live session with @taniachatterjee.official on the 12th of April 2020 at 7:00 PM.
